  <body class="sinai-body">
    {{> templates/google-analytics-body}}
    {{> templates/header}}
    <div id="main">
      <div id="description" class="center-fixed-width">
        <strong>The Sinai Palimpsests Project</strong>
        is using state-of-the-art spectral imaging to recover erased texts from palimpsest manuscripts in the library of
        St. Catherine's Monastery of the Sinai, the world's oldest continually operating monastery. The monastery holds
        an exceptional collection of more than 160 palimpsests, the erased layers of which preserve unstudied texts from
        the 4th to the 12th century. An online research library, now in development, will make the palimpsests of Sinai
        globally accessible for study.
      </div>
